Advanced ATS Resume Optimizer
This project is a BERT-powered resume optimization tool designed to enhance resumes using Natural Language Processing (NLP). It suggests improvements to resume text using a pre-trained BERT model and allows users to download the improved version of their resume.

Features
Upload resumes in .docx format.
Automatically suggest better words using BERT.
View suggestions for resume improvements.
Download the updated resume in .docx format.
Technologies Used
Gradio: For the web interface.
BERT: Pre-trained model for suggesting better words in the resume.
Python-Docx: For reading from and writing to .docx files.
Spacy: For text processing and tokenization.
Transformers: Hugging Face Transformers for loading BERT.
PyTorch: Backend for BERT inference.
Installation & Setup
To get started with this project, follow the steps below:

1. Clone the Repository
bash
Copy code
git clone https://github.com/your-username/Advanced-ATS-Resume-Optimizer.git
cd Advanced-ATS-Resume-Optimizer
2. Install Dependencies
This project requires the following dependencies:

Python 3.7+
Gradio
Transformers
Spacy
PyTorch
Python-Docx
To install the necessary dependencies, run:

bash
Copy code
pip install -r requirements.txt
3. Install Spacy Model
Run the following command to download the English language model for Spacy:

bash
Copy code
python -m spacy download en_core_web_sm
4. Running the Application
To launch the Gradio web interface, run:

bash
Copy code
python app.py
This will start a local server. Open the provided link in your browser to interact with the interface.

5. Usage
Upload your resume in .docx format.
Click Submit to process the resume.
View the improved resume text and suggestions.
Download the updated resume in .docx format.
